  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Previous studies show that one session of tDCS allow to improve muscle strength in
      hemiparetic patients in anodal condition. We test a new electrods configuration : a anodale
      stimulation opposite to the cortical representation area of the injured hemisphere and a
      simultaneous stimulation opposite to the homonyme the cortical representation area of the
      healthy hemisphere. This approach seems to be the best relevant electrods configuration in
      order to restore the inter-hemispheric balance.

      We hypothesis that one session of tDCS with this electrods configuration allow to improve
      paretic quadriceps strength in hemiparetic patients after stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
